SIMPLE: utricular
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utricular
<hw>U*tric"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>utriculaire</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a utricle, or utriculus;
containing, or furnished with, a utricle or utricles; utriculate;
<as>as, a <ex>utricular</ex> plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling a utricle or bag, whether large or
minute; -- said especially with reference to the condition of certain
substances, as sulphur, selenium, etc., when condensed from the vaporous
state and deposited upon cold bodies, in which case they assume the form
of small globules filled with liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utricularia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
